CLOUD COMPUTING
Supply information and comunication tech as services(IT IS MORE THAN SIMPLE VIRTUALIZATION).
PRO
-configurable
-fast provisioned
-dinamic provisioning system (no waste)
-scalable
CONS
-security
-lock-in
-isolation failure
-no deletion

-self service, on demand
-network based access
-pooling
-elastic
-pay per use

------------------------------TYPE-----------------------------------
SERVICE MODEL:
-IaaS: infrastructure (until OS)
-PaaS: platform (until runtime)
-SaaS: software (just software is provided)

DEPLOY MODEL
-PRIVATE: avable just for a group
-PUBLIC: everybody can have an account
-HYBRID: mix 

ISOLATION MODEL
-DEDICATED: dedicated only to specific activities
-MULTI TENANT: con be used for different purposes

--------------------------USE CASE---------------------------
-end user -> cloud
-enterprise -> cloud -> end user
-enterprise -> cloud
-enterprise -> cloud -> enterprise


-production migration
-traffic bursting
-backup
-web osting
-testing
-big data manipulation

----------------------APPLICATION-----------------------------
-STATELESS: do not store info           => BEST ON CLOUD
-STATEFUL: provide responses on tha base of previous state























